ol'; font-size: 1.375em; font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.16em; margin: 1e=
m 0 0.625em 0; position: relative;"><strong>The Right Level of Integration =
is Not Obvious</strong></h3><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>I started Part II with =
a story about </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/4cf0d393-4d2a=
-4458-ad6e-3f58716e69fb?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbq=
Osa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: unde=
rline;">Hadrian</a><span> to make one point: software alone isn&#8217;t usu=
ally enough to solve the problem. What I didn&#8217;t cover is that </span>=
<em><strong>too much</strong></em><strong> vertical integration, too soon, =
is an issue, too.</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54,=
 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>In=
 that </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/4cf0d393-4d2a-4458-ad=
6e-3f58716e69fb?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8=
ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); text-decoration: underline;">=
Deep Dive on Hadrian</a><span>, I highlighted that two of the company&#8217=
;s lead investors, Lux and Founders Fund, had previously backed a company t=
rying to automate parts manufacturing: Plethora. The company, founded in 20=
13 to build the </span><strong>factory of the future</strong><span> by crea=
ting &#8220;a manufacturing system that turns customer designs into custom =
parts using robotics and advanced software that we&#8217;ve developed in-ho=
use,&#8221; failed.&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); fon=
t-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">There were three less=
ons from Plethora&#8217;s failure, according to investors and former employ=
ees:</p><ul style=3D"margin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0=
 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; c=
olor: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margi=
n-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><em><span>They tried to do </span><strong>=
everything in software, </strong><span>cutting the humans out of the loop, =
which meant years of wasted time trying to solve &#8220;</span><strong>hobb=
y problems</strong><span>&#8221; that humans could easily do.</span></em></=
p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"><p s=
tyle=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><em><span=
>The offering was </span><strong>too broad</strong><span> &#8211; from prot=
otypes to parts, different materials, different shapes, high-end and low-en=
d, not precision-focused &#8211; Plethora wanted to do everything.</span></=
em></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;"=
><p style=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><em>=
<span>It was a little </span><strong>too early</strong><span>, both in term=
s of customer demand for high-precision parts and in terms of the financing=
 market for a business like this.</span></em></p></li></ul><p style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
"><span>In short: </span><strong>Plethora tried to do too much, too soon, t=
oo early.</strong><span>&#160;</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55)=
; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">This rhymes with=
 Katerra&#8217;s failure: too much, too soon, if not too early (people will=
 always want cheaper houses).&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); =
font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Katerra also likel=
y vertically integrated too deep into the materials supply chain. As Potter=
 points out, the company invested ~$100 million into a Cross-Laminated Timb=
er (CLT) factory that could produce ~10% of the world&#8217;s supply of CLT=
=2E In addition to being a big investme=
nt of limited resources, it locked the=
 company into a product that he said ended up getting cut out of plans in v=
alue engineering too often because it&#8217;s an expensive material.&#160;<=
/p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; =
margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>A lesson might be this: </span><strong>verticall=
y integrate to whatever level will give you the best product at the lowest =
cost (lower than legacy alternatives) before integrating further with scale=
=2E&#160;</strong></p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; li=
ne-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">But that&#8217;s about a billion time=
s easier to write than it is to do.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55,=
 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">Plethora lik=
ely believed that fully automating would let it produce the best products a=
t the lowest cost before running into all of the challenges of actually bui=
lding a fully automated manufacturing process. Katerra likely believed that=
 its breadth and ownership of the supply chain were these interlinked thing=
s that, if everything went just right, would allow it to achieve the scale =
required to build the best product at the lowest cost. </p><p style=3D"colo=
r: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;=
">There&#8217;s probably no shortcut but experimentation at fast iteration =
speed. You need to form a hypothesis, try it out, and adjust. The problem i=
s, unlike software, the &#8220;minimum viable product&#8221; requires a ton=
 of commitment in one direction.&#160;</p><h3 class=3D"header-anchor-post" =
style=3D"--highlight-bg: rgba(var(--color-bg-accent-themed-rgb), 0.2); -moz=
-appearance: optimizelegibility; -moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased; -web=
